<title>IRAN: Iran calls for stronger OPEC to prevent market chaOS.</title>
<headline>Iran calls for stronger OPEC to prevent market chaOS.</headline>
<dateline>ISFAHAN, Iran 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Iran's Oil Minister Gholamreza Aghazadeh called on Thursday for a stronger OPEC.</p>
<p>&quot;Being the only effective economic organisation in the developing world, OPEC should be strengthened and its shortcomings must be overcome,&quot; he told an energy conference here.</p>
<p>&quot;The absence of OPEC will lead to chaos in the oil market,&quot; he said. &quot;Experience has shown that capitalism's dominance and laissez-faire policies have not only been harmful at times, but they have contributed to severe dislocations and inequalities in the world economy.&quot;</p>
</text>
